article.headline: Delaware 17, Hofstra 0
article.story: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. -- Junior Jabbie ran for 155 yards and a touchdown to help Delaware halt a three-game losing streak with a 17-0 victory over Hofstra in a rain-soaked game on Saturday. Robbie Agnone had a 1-yard touchdown catch and Jon Striefski kicked a 27-yard field goal for the Blue Hens (3-5, 1-3 Colonial). The Pride (3-5, 1-3) lost for the third time in four games. Steve Probst was 11-for-28 for 71 yards for Hofstra. He was intercepted twice and sacked five times. Andrew Harrison and Matt Marcorelle each had two sacks for the Blue Hens.
